title: 820-3209-A Green Light - Not Powering ON
message:
Greetings from Australia !

This is my first post please be gentle ... however I'm ready to get fucked ..

I've got a Macbook Air 13" A1466 820-3209-A. I'm getting the green light on MagSafe (adapter sense working) however I'm getting no chime and no fan spinning.

I've tested all major power rails and believe the board to be in a "S0" state. 

What should I test next? Thanks

title: 820-3209-A Green Light - Not Powering ON
message:
Find the rail that's missing. You said you tested all major power rails, but it is not turning on, which means there is a power rail that is missing. Ignore TBT rails since they are for thunderbolt.

Also, you said you believe the board is in an S0 state. Are S0 power rails present?
